# {{context|computing|lang=en}} In the design of a [[database]] [[table]], the primary key (abbreviated [[PK]]) is selected among the non-empty set of [[candidate key]]s. The PK is a [[column]] (or an [[irreducible]] group of columns) able to uniquely identify every [[row]] of the table. 

